01:01.687 --> 01:06.275
JAKE:
<i>In the summer of 2002, I was 19 years old.</i>

01:07.109 --> 01:10.196
<i>Lived my whole life
in Bridgeton, Washington.</i>

01:11.322 --> 01:14.742
<i>After high school, I did what everybody
did: worked at the lumber mill.</i>

01:18.996 --> 01:21.082
<i>But unlike most people here
who never leave...</i>

01:21.832 --> 01:24.126
<i>...I knew I wanted something more.</i>

01:24.293 --> 01:28.172
<i>Something to get me out of Bridgeton
and also serve my country.</i>

01:30.841 --> 01:34.386
<i>So I enlisted
in the United States Marine Corps.</i>

01:46.524 --> 01:48.692
<i>It was the toughest training of my life.</i>

01:48.859 --> 01:50.694
<i>We prepared for everything.</i>

01:51.278 --> 01:55.366
<i>By land, sea or air.</i>

01:55.533 --> 01:58.536
<i>Wherever combat may be,
Marines are prepared.</i>

02:06.001 --> 02:08.378
<i>It wasn't just about
achieving your goals...</i>

02:08.545 --> 02:10.714
<i>...but about believing in yourself.</i>

02:13.676 --> 02:15.553
(GUNFIRE)

02:16.220 --> 02:19.306
<i>Our motto: Semper Fi.</i>

02:19.473 --> 02:21.976
<i>Always faithful. Always loyal.</i>

02:22.143 --> 02:23.602
<i>To your comrades in arms.</i>

02:23.769 --> 02:25.062
<i>To your country.</i>

02:25.229 --> 02:27.064
<i>To your family.</i>

02:47.793 --> 02:48.919
<i>I saw the world.</i>

02:49.086 --> 02:51.422
<i>For more than 10 years,
I moved about the globe.</i>

02:51.589 --> 02:54.758
<i>Missions. Deployments. War.</i>

03:11.525 --> 03:14.403
<i>Every now and again, you get to take leave.</i>

03:15.029 --> 03:17.948
<i>My folks passed away a few years back.</i>

03:18.407 --> 03:23.078
<i>Family for me now is just my two sisters,
Lilly and Amanda.</i>

03:23.370 --> 03:28.667
<i>It's been over 14 months
and today I'm going home.</i>

03:31.879 --> 03:34.882
(KEN JOHNSON, AL ANDERSON
& ADAM ZELKIND'S "NEW PAINT" PLAYING)

03:37.134 --> 03:42.056
<i>Not a whole lot's changed
Since I've been gone</i>

03:43.724 --> 03:47.728
<i>Same old band
Still plays the same old songs</i>

03:49.772 --> 03:55.194
<i>Yeah, this hole-in-the-wall dive bar
Don't ever get old</i>

03:56.570 --> 04:01.533
<i>Oh, they never did sell out
And I'm still sold</i>

04:02.952 --> 04:06.580
<i>Hello, my friend
How long's it been?</i>

04:06.747 --> 04:10.084
<i>Yesterdays are here again</i>

04:10.251 --> 04:15.422
<i>Shoot the moon
Till that big old ball falls down</i>

04:16.966 --> 04:19.718
<i>Small-town boys haven't changed their ways</i>

04:19.885 --> 04:23.222
<i>Still livin' in the glory days</i>

04:23.389 --> 04:27.601
<i>Same old stories
Just keep getting better somehow</i>

04:27.768 --> 04:32.523
<i>It's time to put a fresh coat of new paint
On this old town</i>

04:45.119 --> 04:49.039
<i>Well, I remember not so long ago</i>

04:51.125 --> 04:56.046
<i>The newness of that old familiar glow</i>

04:57.006 --> 05:03.053
<i>Yeah, these neon lights
Have got that same old buzz</i>

05:04.138 --> 05:09.768
<i>This place is what it is
And what it was</i>

05:10.894 --> 05:13.981
<i>Hello, my friend
How long's it been?</i>

05:14.148 --> 05:17.318
<i>Yesterdays are here again</i>

05:17.484 --> 05:22.406
<i>Shoot the moon
Till that big old ball falls down</i>

05:23.866 --> 05:27.077
<i>Some folks still haven't changed their ways</i>

05:27.244 --> 05:30.581
<i>Still livin' in the glory days</i>

05:30.748 --> 05:35.252
<i>Same old stories
Just keep getting better somehow</i>

05:35.419 --> 05:40.174
<i>It's time to put a fresh coat of new paint
On this old town</i>

05:52.770 --> 05:54.772
(BELL TOLLING IN DISTANCE)

05:55.773 --> 05:57.608
You lost, boy?

06:02.279 --> 06:05.866
Your daddy know you're out playing cop?
Now you take a good look, smartass.

06:06.033 --> 06:07.242
Chief.

06:07.409 --> 06:08.619
Of what? Mall security?

06:09.620 --> 06:12.456
Marine or not, I will kick your ass.

06:12.623 --> 06:14.208
Huh?
Come here.

06:16.543 --> 06:18.295
Well, how you doing, man?
Good. You?

06:18.462 --> 06:20.255
I can't complain. I try not to.

06:20.422 --> 06:24.635
Just look at you, pal. You're looking good.
Real good. A little heavy, but healthy.

06:25.177 --> 06:26.970
You know.
You look as dumb as ever.

06:27.137 --> 06:29.223
Yeah, well, what do you do?
Yeah.

06:29.807 --> 06:32.643
So how long are you home for?
Two weeks.

06:32.810 --> 06:37.189
More than enough time for you and me
to get in trouble. Come on. Car's this way.

06:37.356 --> 06:38.690
(GRUNTS)

06:39.066 --> 06:40.359
What happened to Woody's?

06:40.526 --> 06:43.028
HARKIN:
Went to shit when his kid took over.

06:48.951 --> 06:50.494
MAN:
Let's head it up.

06:53.539 --> 06:56.125
Jeez. This thing steers like
a nightmare. It's unbelievable.

06:56.291 --> 06:57.876
Well, it is a piece of junk.
Yeah.

06:58.043 --> 07:01.088
Can't get anything new?
Bridgeton can't afford a new truck?

07:01.255 --> 07:04.091
HARKIN: Bridgeton can't afford shit, man.
You know that.

07:07.553 --> 07:10.848
You seen my little sister running around?
Time to time.

07:12.057 --> 07:14.935
How's she doing?
Lilly's Lilly. You know? She's having fun.

07:15.102 --> 07:17.020
She's looking for a job right now.
For a job?

07:17.187 --> 07:19.106
Mm-hm.
I thought you set her up at Creston's?

07:19.273 --> 07:23.026
I did. Went pretty good
for a couple weeks there too, but...

07:23.193 --> 07:25.654
Then she went and told old Cresty
to go fuck himself.

07:25.821 --> 07:28.449
She told Cresty to go fuck himself?
That's so you know.

07:28.615 --> 07:31.201
Lilly's Lilly.
Yeah, Lilly is Lilly.

07:31.368 --> 07:34.371
(SUNDAY JONES' "UP & DOWN" PLAYING)

07:35.539 --> 07:39.710
Whoa. Amanda.
Cooking school has not paid off.

07:39.877 --> 07:41.670
(BOTH LAUGHING)

07:42.379 --> 07:46.300
<i>Soon the time is only hours</i>

07:46.467 --> 07:50.053
<i>That we'll be going home again</i>

07:50.220 --> 07:51.805
(HORN HONKS)

07:53.390 --> 07:55.017
AMANDA:
There he is.

07:56.268 --> 07:59.062
(BOTH LAUGH)

08:00.856 --> 08:03.734
Oh.
Oh, it's so good to see you in one piece.

08:03.901 --> 08:05.819
You look great.
You look good.

08:06.111 --> 08:08.572
I don't know about this. No.
You don't know about this?

08:08.739 --> 08:10.619
LILLY: I love it!
JAKE: Get over... You love it?

08:10.741 --> 08:13.202
(LILLY LAUGHING)

08:17.080 --> 08:18.749
JAKE:
Your hair's gotten longer.

08:18.916 --> 08:21.668
Yours has too.
You staying out of trouble?

08:21.835 --> 08:22.920
Hmm.
Hmm?

08:23.086 --> 08:24.755
What do you need?
What can I get you?

08:24.922 --> 08:27.799
A cold beer.
Done.

08:32.054 --> 08:33.679
Cheers.
Cheers.

08:33.847 --> 08:35.432
Here's to coming home in one piece.

08:38.101 --> 08:42.147
Plenty more where that came from. They can't
wait to see the local celebrity down at the bar.

08:42.313 --> 08:43.398
(LILLY LAUGHS)

08:43.565 --> 08:46.443
AMANDA: I got burgers. I got ribs.
The ribs are done in, like, 10.

08:46.610 --> 08:48.403
The burgers are pretty much ready now.

08:48.570 --> 08:50.447
HARKIN: I think they were ready
about 10 minutes ago.

08:50.614 --> 08:53.158
(ALL LAUGHING AND CHATTERING)

08:53.325 --> 08:55.786
Maybe stay away from the burgers.
HARKIN: We got lots more.

08:55.953 --> 08:59.790
I made potato salad. I've got pie.
I got pecan and...

08:59.957 --> 09:04.127
Whoa, whoa. Trying to fatten me up already?
That's what I do. I gotta fatten you up.

09:04.836 --> 09:06.880
LILLY:
Here, have more.

09:07.422 --> 09:08.715
I'm good.

09:09.132 --> 09:10.133
(CHUCKLES)

09:11.510 --> 09:14.429
Mom and Dad been asking about you.
How's Bernie and Gernie?

09:14.596 --> 09:16.640
Starting to think they love you
more than me.

09:16.807 --> 09:18.809
Of course they do.
What's Bernie been up to?

09:18.976 --> 09:20.811
HARKIN: Golf. You believe that?
JAKE: Really?

09:21.019 --> 09:22.646
Golfing?
Must be a quick learner.

09:22.813 --> 09:24.690
He's about a 12 handicap.
Twelve?

09:24.856 --> 09:26.900
HARKIN: Guess what mom is.
JAKE: What?

09:27.067 --> 09:29.027
Nine.
Heh, heh, heh.

09:29.403 --> 09:33.448
Bernie must be pissed.
Yeah. Dad's losing sleep over it too.

09:33.615 --> 09:36.535
Speaking of losing sleep,
how are you sleeping?

09:36.702 --> 09:39.079
I'm sleeping.
That is a complete lie.

09:39.663 --> 09:42.374
What about you? Still crawling out
the window at midnight?

09:42.541 --> 09:43.917
I'm still coming home at 4 a.m.

09:44.084 --> 09:45.919
(ALL CHUCKLING)

09:49.756 --> 09:50.924
How's work?

09:54.553 --> 09:57.264
Good.
You and Cresty getting along?

09:57.431 --> 10:00.392
LILLY: Swimmingly.
Swimmingly, huh?

10:01.351 --> 10:04.521
I heard you told him to go fuck himself.

10:07.524 --> 10:11.236
Um... Cresty's an asshole.

10:12.070 --> 10:15.866
He's an asshole, but he gave you a job.
Later, Jake. It's not a big deal.

10:16.033 --> 10:18.869
It's not a big deal?
You gonna find her another job?

10:19.828 --> 10:21.830
I'll go check on that meat.

10:22.831 --> 10:24.708
Welcome home.

10:25.208 --> 10:26.501
You big buzz kill.

10:42.142 --> 10:44.144
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

10:51.735 --> 10:53.445
Mrs. Swanson.
Yes?

10:53.612 --> 10:57.658
I'm running a bit behind today. I told
Mr. Vidier I was gonna push him 12 minutes.

10:57.824 --> 10:59.701
So that bumps everyone else down.
Sure.

10:59.868 --> 11:01.411
I had to drop off the kids today.

11:01.578 --> 11:05.248
So can you push everyone down
15 minutes and call my trainer.

11:05.415 --> 11:08.251
See if she can get me in at 12:15.
I should be done by then.

11:08.418 --> 11:10.045
I should be all caught up.

11:10.212 --> 11:12.255
My wife called...

11:16.593 --> 11:19.846
On the fucking ground or die!

11:20.013 --> 11:22.224
MAN 1: Move it!
MAN 2: Everybody down!

11:22.391 --> 11:25.102
Get down on the ground!
MAN 3: Get on the ground! Move!

11:25.268 --> 11:26.603
Move!

11:26.770 --> 11:28.689
(MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

11:30.899 --> 11:33.360
Everyone remain calm and quiet.

11:34.152 --> 11:39.741
If you move or make any sound,
you will die.

11:45.288 --> 11:47.541
You. Up.

11:57.134 --> 11:59.344
Brendon and Liam.

11:59.511 --> 12:01.263
Grades three and five.

12:01.430 --> 12:03.056
Centerville Elementary School.

12:03.223 --> 12:07.102
Your wife, Lynn? She's at Pilates till 10
where she goes every Tuesday and Thursday.

12:07.269 --> 12:11.732
Then she goes to her part-time gig
at Our Lady of Victory Church.

12:11.898 --> 12:14.276
You have a beautiful family, Glen.

12:14.443 --> 12:18.488
But they will all be dead by day's end
if you do not cooperate with me fully.

12:18.655 --> 12:19.656
Do you understand?

12:20.198 --> 12:21.241
Mm-hm.

12:21.908 --> 12:26.329
Have your tellers open their drawers
and give the cash to my men now.

12:26.496 --> 12:27.998
Ms. Swanson. Ms. Swanson?

12:28.165 --> 12:30.834
Have your tellers give these men
anything that they want.

12:31.001 --> 12:32.419
Right now.
Okay.

12:32.836 --> 12:34.629
POPE:
Say it loud or she dies.

12:34.796 --> 12:38.341
Ms. Swanson, have them open the drawers
and give the men the money. Now.

12:38.508 --> 12:39.634
Now! Now!

12:45.390 --> 12:47.893
MAN 2: Hurry up!
MAN 1: Open the fucking drawers.

12:50.228 --> 12:51.772
TELLER:
Okay, okay!

12:59.237 --> 13:01.114
I don't like bankers.

13:02.199 --> 13:04.034
I'm a regional manager.

13:04.201 --> 13:06.328
I don't make decisions. I follow orders.

13:07.621 --> 13:11.208
How many houses
have you foreclosed on this year?

13:11.374 --> 13:14.002
How many?

13:14.377 --> 13:16.171
Too many.

13:16.379 --> 13:18.548
Too many.
You know why?

13:19.508 --> 13:21.510
It's greed, Glen.

13:22.052 --> 13:25.263
Greed, people. It's a disease...

13:25.430 --> 13:30.060
...that is eating away at our nation
from the top down.

13:31.645 --> 13:34.356
Personal responsibility.
That's what builds a nation.

13:38.401 --> 13:41.363
You take what you need.

13:41.530 --> 13:44.866
No more. No less.

13:57.921 --> 13:59.005
Let's go.

14:18.400 --> 14:20.402
(SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)

14:41.715 --> 14:43.842
They'd be so proud of you.

14:44.509 --> 14:46.845
Now me, not so much.

14:47.137 --> 14:49.848
Divorced. No kids. Broke.

14:51.308 --> 14:54.978
Property tax is killing me,
and I may have to sell the place.

14:55.145 --> 14:59.065
It's just... It's too big for me and Lilly
and it doesn't make sense.

15:02.652 --> 15:04.779
How much do you need?
No. You've done enough.

15:04.946 --> 15:07.032
We live here. We'll pay the bills.
How much?

15:07.198 --> 15:09.492
Mandy, have you seen my boots?

15:09.659 --> 15:11.786
They're on the porch.
They were covered in mud.

15:11.953 --> 15:13.997
That's why they're called
boots, not slippers.

15:14.164 --> 15:15.165
You wear them outdoors.

15:15.332 --> 15:18.627
Getting dressed around here
is like a frigging Easter egg hunt.

15:21.546 --> 15:25.175
Has she thought about taking classes again?
You can have that chat tomorrow.

15:25.342 --> 15:27.886
She'd love to give you her thoughts
on higher education.

15:28.053 --> 15:30.764
Christ, Amanda.
She's gotta do something with herself.

15:30.931 --> 15:33.850
Have you even talked to her about...?
Enough, Jake. I'm tired.

15:34.017 --> 15:35.518
I just want to relax.

15:36.394 --> 15:38.146
LILLY:
Okay.

15:38.313 --> 15:41.691
Bye.
I'll see you guys later.

15:41.858 --> 15:43.526
Where you going?

15:44.569 --> 15:45.820
Out.

15:45.987 --> 15:47.864
Darren's waiting.
Darren?

15:48.031 --> 15:50.450
Darren Carlyle. Miller's kid.
You remember him.

15:50.617 --> 15:52.243
I remember not liking him.

15:52.410 --> 15:56.331
Jake, relax. Please. He's a good guy.

15:56.498 --> 15:59.250
He's not some idiot
like the rest of the losers around here.

15:59.417 --> 16:02.045
Didn't he go to juvie for selling weed?
Years ago.

16:02.212 --> 16:04.130
I...

16:04.297 --> 16:05.882
...love you.

16:06.049 --> 16:07.509
So much.

16:08.218 --> 16:09.636
Bye.

16:12.764 --> 16:13.807
You're real subtle.

16:14.933 --> 16:16.184
It's a gift.

16:18.395 --> 16:20.563
Hey, baby.
Hey, you.

16:20.730 --> 16:22.399
Come here.

16:22.899 --> 16:24.234
Mm.

16:25.735 --> 16:28.071
Wow. You look nice.

16:29.406 --> 16:30.907
Thanks.

16:43.378 --> 16:46.464
I noticed your brother's back.
Yep.

16:47.090 --> 16:49.592
He still got a stick up his ass?
Yep.

16:53.805 --> 16:56.099
He never liked me much anyways.

16:56.266 --> 16:57.809
Let's just go.

16:57.976 --> 17:01.604
Hey, Darren, come on in for a sec.
Have a beer or something.

17:01.771 --> 17:05.692
Um...
Jake, you're not my dad. Okay?

17:06.276 --> 17:08.028
Roger that?

17:08.194 --> 17:09.695
Let's go. Now.

17:10.280 --> 17:12.656
Go. Come on. Please. Drive.

17:12.824 --> 17:14.576
(THE GENDERS' "VIRGIN NO. 72"
PLAYING OVER STEREO)

17:14.742 --> 17:17.579
Come on. Let's go. Whoa!

17:17.746 --> 17:20.415
<i>Be my virgin number 72</i>

17:20.582 --> 17:23.292
LILLY:
Whoo!

17:35.555 --> 17:37.766
POPE:
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

17:39.642 --> 17:42.520
Well, that's interesting. Yeah.

17:42.687 --> 17:46.149
That's the kind of news
I could have used last week.

17:50.987 --> 17:52.322
Problem?

17:52.489 --> 17:54.491
Summit's been moved up.

17:54.657 --> 17:56.117
Tomorrow afternoon.

17:56.993 --> 17:59.079
We can be ready.
The RDX?

17:59.245 --> 18:02.123
I'll talk to Eckert.
His boys can make it by morning.

18:03.124 --> 18:04.584
All right. Let's make it work.

18:06.503 --> 18:07.837
MAN 1:
Clear.

18:08.213 --> 18:09.839
(ENGINE STARTS)

18:11.883 --> 18:14.177
MAN 2: Disable that sensor.
You don't need it anyway.

18:14.844 --> 18:16.721
MAN 3:
Almost there.

18:19.933 --> 18:21.518
Jackson, give them their bit.

18:22.602 --> 18:25.939
No more, no less.
MAN 4: Payday, boys, payday.

18:26.106 --> 18:28.191
A change of plans.

18:29.025 --> 18:31.653
We move tomorrow.
Late afternoon.

18:31.820 --> 18:34.697
Which means this car needs
to be ready by morning.

18:34.864 --> 18:38.076
And the RDX rigged as soon
as possible.

18:40.370 --> 18:43.832
How about you start telling us
what the actual game plan is?

18:45.250 --> 18:48.253
Your lap dog over there
seems to know everything.

18:49.254 --> 18:51.172
I know him. I trust him.

18:53.049 --> 18:55.218
Well, that's just cute.

18:56.678 --> 18:58.555
Congratulations to you.

18:58.721 --> 19:00.849
But we've all put our ass on the line.

19:01.015 --> 19:02.142
And don't forget:

19:02.308 --> 19:05.103
They're my contacts
that are gonna score us the RDX.

19:05.270 --> 19:07.230
Not yours.

19:07.814 --> 19:09.315
Not his.

19:09.774 --> 19:11.317
Mine.

19:11.484 --> 19:13.695
You ground us.
You take our phones away.

19:13.862 --> 19:16.906
You put us in a little corner
and lock us up in here like convicts.

19:17.073 --> 19:19.701
I'm getting sick of working
with blinders on.

19:19.868 --> 19:21.703
Blinders on?
Yeah.

19:22.912 --> 19:26.958
For the integrity of the mission, I haven't
done anything that we haven't agreed to.

19:27.125 --> 19:28.585
Integrity?

19:30.086 --> 19:34.591
"The integrity of the mission."
I like that. No, I do.

19:35.091 --> 19:37.677
This coming from a guy
who gets all bent out of shape...

19:37.844 --> 19:41.556
...when we take a step outside to get
a breath of fresh air from this shit-hole.

19:41.723 --> 19:45.101
But it's all for the integrity
of the mission.

19:45.268 --> 19:47.353
Yeah, I get it. Okay.

19:47.520 --> 19:51.274
Oh, yeah. One more thing,
that's bullshit.

19:52.317 --> 19:55.195
Christ, Eckert, I get it.

19:55.361 --> 19:59.240
Pope don't trust us.
Hell, he don't trust no one.

19:59.407 --> 20:01.784
Don't take it so personal.
No, I get it too.

20:01.951 --> 20:04.454
I am all for the cause.

20:05.038 --> 20:07.123
Things in this country are fucked up.
Mm-hm.

20:07.290 --> 20:09.626
But I want you to know one thing.

20:10.001 --> 20:13.296
I'm not some monkey that's gonna do
a dance every time the music plays.

20:13.463 --> 20:16.591
I'm gonna ask you one more time.
What's the target?

20:19.052 --> 20:22.138
By day's end tomorrow, you will know.

20:30.730 --> 20:33.733
(THE MOTHER TRUCKERS' "BREAK-UP SEX"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS)

20:39.239 --> 20:41.324
<i>You ain't never home</i>

20:41.741 --> 20:43.534
All right, see you, man.

20:46.871 --> 20:48.456
What'd I tell you?

20:48.706 --> 20:51.459
Hey. Can I get a beer, man?
Payton.

20:51.626 --> 20:54.212
Jake. Hey, man.
How's it going?

20:54.379 --> 20:56.214
Good. Just got back.
How you been?

20:56.381 --> 20:59.008
Ah. Awful. Hey. Let me get you a drink.
Awful?

20:59.175 --> 21:02.095
No, I'm good. I'm just waiting on Hark.
Have you seen him?

21:02.303 --> 21:03.846
No. No, I haven't.

21:04.722 --> 21:06.975
Cheers.
Cheers.

21:14.065 --> 21:16.818
Mm. I see Twig's here.
Twig's here?

21:16.985 --> 21:18.695
Yeah, in the back.

21:20.029 --> 21:22.240
What is it, like family night?

21:24.951 --> 21:27.787
Man, seeing you again,
it reminds me of my little brother.

21:27.954 --> 21:30.206
How's Petey doing?
Oh, terrible.

21:30.373 --> 21:33.293
He married some ugly girl.
Sounds like Petey.

21:33.459 --> 21:35.086
(LAUGHS)

21:35.253 --> 21:38.548
KIRK: Dude, give me a little bit of room here.
What is your problem?

21:38.715 --> 21:41.092
Dude, I ain't got no problem.
You got a problem?

21:41.884 --> 21:44.178
Just fucking beat it, man.

21:45.680 --> 21:48.057
Back the fuck off.
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Calm down.

21:48.224 --> 21:51.102
All right?
How about we call it a night?

21:51.269 --> 21:53.730
You know, he's kind of drunk.
You know?

21:56.316 --> 21:57.567
Mother...!

22:00.069 --> 22:01.070
(GROANS)

22:02.071 --> 22:04.741
Jesus fucking Christ, Jake.

22:18.463 --> 22:20.965
(KIRK COUGHING)

22:30.308 --> 22:32.310
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

22:43.154 --> 22:47.200
Before you say anything... If we weren't
pals, you'd be in jail right now.

22:50.286 --> 22:53.331
So let me get this straight.

22:53.498 --> 22:56.125
You come home.
You tell Amanda how to run the house.

22:56.292 --> 22:58.753
You disapprove of Lilly's lifestyle.
Look at me, dude.

22:58.920 --> 23:01.130
And the boyfriend.
You hate him too.

23:01.297 --> 23:03.549
You know...
Don't talk.

23:03.841 --> 23:05.009
So then what?

23:05.176 --> 23:08.179
You come down for a cold one
and brutalize a redneck?

23:08.346 --> 23:11.474
I've had better days.
If you are going to come home...

23:11.641 --> 23:15.103
...you're gonna have to learn how
to assimilate to normal society.

23:20.316 --> 23:23.611
Look, Lilly's dating a punk.
His name's Darren.

23:23.778 --> 23:25.988
He's actually a pretty nice kid.
He's a loser.

23:26.155 --> 23:28.616
You're a broken record.
Who do you want her dating?

23:28.783 --> 23:30.410
A neurosurgeon?
Rocket scientist?

23:30.576 --> 23:32.286
What do you want? This is Bridgeton.

23:33.329 --> 23:35.998
Are you gonna take this guy home?
Do I have to?

23:36.165 --> 23:38.084
For the sake of
the civilized world, yes.

23:38.251 --> 23:41.963
Now, if you'll excuse me, I've gotta go see
a gentleman about his missing teeth.

23:42.130 --> 23:44.173
Call me later.
Yeah.

23:46.759 --> 23:48.553
Call me later?

23:49.470 --> 23:52.014
Hark and I have been
seeing each other a bit.

23:55.017 --> 23:56.519
You've been seeing Hark.

23:56.686 --> 23:59.897
You know what's funny? You don't
even approve of your own best friend.

24:00.064 --> 24:02.525
You come home every time
like a bull in a china shop.

24:02.692 --> 24:05.278
Me, Hark, Lilly,
we love you to death but...

24:05.445 --> 24:07.196
You gotta let this go, Jake.

24:07.363 --> 24:10.158
We don't need a protector.
We're all grown up here.

24:11.367 --> 24:15.037
Do you want a ride or don't you?
Yes.

24:17.540 --> 24:19.292
(TRAIN HORN BLARING)

24:20.001 --> 24:22.321
LILLY: You ready?
DARREN: Just give me a couple of minutes.

24:22.462 --> 24:25.631
I'll get you out of this junkyard.
Gotta find this connector.

24:25.798 --> 24:27.216
Cool?

24:27.383 --> 24:29.552
(THE CANVAS WAITING'S
"AN ISLAND NOW" PLAYING)

24:30.761 --> 24:35.433
<i>Stand tall and proud
On your rusty bow</i>

24:36.058 --> 24:37.477
You all right?

24:37.643 --> 24:40.146
<i>The sight of land won't let you down</i>

24:40.313 --> 24:41.606
Mm.

24:42.732 --> 24:44.066
What's on your mind?

24:44.233 --> 24:46.903
<i>When the fog has cleared
I'm an island now</i>

24:47.069 --> 24:48.821
Do you want to stay here forever?

24:49.906 --> 24:51.032
Here?

24:51.199 --> 24:54.160
No, just gotta get this
battery connector off,

24:54.327 --> 24:56.746
then we can get the hell
out of here.

24:56.913 --> 24:59.957
No. I meant here in Bridgeton.

25:00.124 --> 25:02.919
Oh. Heh.

25:03.878 --> 25:06.506
No. Not really.

25:06.672 --> 25:08.257
Why not?

25:09.091 --> 25:10.676
Not sure where I'd go.

25:11.177 --> 25:13.179
Yeah, me neither.

25:13.346 --> 25:16.390
My brother wants
to get to know you better.

25:16.807 --> 25:19.101
Wants to have you over
for dinner.

25:20.895 --> 25:23.272
<i>'Cause I fall sleep with dignity</i>

25:23.439 --> 25:25.107
(CAN OPENS)

25:25.274 --> 25:26.734
<i>And you're safe</i>

25:26.901 --> 25:27.944
Fuck that.

25:28.361 --> 25:32.907
<i>'Cause you filled that hole
Before it was empty</i>

25:33.074 --> 25:35.826
You know military guys
remind me of my stepdad.

25:35.993 --> 25:37.036
I know.

25:37.203 --> 25:39.455
You know,
it's that "do this, do that" attitude.

25:39.622 --> 25:43.668
"Cut your hair. Go to school.
Get a job."

25:44.669 --> 25:46.504
It's never good enough.

25:47.129 --> 25:50.466
Even when I get a fucking job,
I gotta get a better one.

25:51.300 --> 25:54.887
<i>I thought I heard bells
But I confused the sound</i>

25:55.054 --> 25:56.138
Hey.

25:57.765 --> 25:59.141
Come on.

25:59.767 --> 26:02.895
<i>I'm an island now</i>

26:09.944 --> 26:11.404
Yeah.

26:28.170 --> 26:29.839
All right, you two stay back.

26:30.006 --> 26:32.508
Keep your eyes open. I don't
trust this guy. ECKERT: Oh.

26:33.551 --> 26:35.845
Surprise, surprise.

26:36.012 --> 26:37.972
Do you trust him?

26:38.639 --> 26:40.600
His stuff is legit.

26:40.766 --> 26:42.518
I trust that.
We'll see.

26:42.685 --> 26:44.186
Let's go.

26:47.189 --> 26:48.357
(SNAPS FINGERS)

27:05.207 --> 27:06.959
Eckert.

27:07.418 --> 27:08.878
Let's take a look.

27:09.045 --> 27:12.131
He's all business. Ha.

27:12.298 --> 27:14.300
I like that.

27:16.761 --> 27:19.680
USDA prime cut.

27:20.431 --> 27:21.849
Check it out.

27:29.065 --> 27:30.983
Looks good.
Good.

27:31.567 --> 27:33.653
What did I tell you?

27:40.660 --> 27:43.120
You might want to hold on there.

27:43.663 --> 27:46.040
Gentlemen, I think we have a problem.

27:46.207 --> 27:49.835
I don't like problems.
Shit, neither do I.

27:50.586 --> 27:53.089
The change in schedule
was a real pain in my ass.

28:00.262 --> 28:02.556
What the fuck's going on up there?
I don't know.

28:02.723 --> 28:04.934
Rush order comes with a price.

28:05.101 --> 28:07.144
What you've got in your hands
is what you get.

28:07.311 --> 28:08.938
We had a deal. Right?

28:09.105 --> 28:13.734
That was the deal. Look, I understand,
y'all don't like a curve ball.

28:14.151 --> 28:19.949
If you need time to think about it, we can
put this off to tomorrow or the next day.

28:20.116 --> 28:21.367
Can't wait till tomorrow.

28:23.285 --> 28:24.495
(LILLY GASPS)

28:25.287 --> 28:26.956
Holy shit.
It's okay, it's okay.

28:29.041 --> 28:31.711
Eckert, you son of a bitch.

28:32.545 --> 28:33.963
(LILLY SCREAMS)

28:34.130 --> 28:37.258
Get down.
Go!

28:37.425 --> 28:39.885
Let's go. Get in the car.
Go, go, go.

28:52.898 --> 28:55.901
Hey, what's up?
Amanda, it's me. I just saw a shooting.

28:56.068 --> 28:58.404
Come on, baby. Come on!
Get it going! No, I'm with Darren.

28:58.571 --> 28:59.613
(ENGINE FALTERING)

28:59.780 --> 29:02.408
It's three guys, and they
just shot him in the head.

29:02.575 --> 29:06.495
Just calm down and tell me where you are.
We're at Grayson's junkyard.

29:06.662 --> 29:07.663
Yeah, by the river.

29:11.333 --> 29:12.793
Shit.

29:13.252 --> 29:15.963
Go, go, go. Fuck.

29:22.845 --> 29:24.847
(VIBRATING)

29:28.726 --> 29:30.567
What's up?
AMANDA: <i>Jake, Lilly just called me.</i>

29:30.728 --> 29:34.190
She was screaming, crying.
She said that she saw somebody get shot.

29:34.356 --> 29:38.235
She... Something's wrong. Something's wrong.
I called Hark, but he didn't answer.

29:38.402 --> 29:41.363
Where?
<i>Grayson's junkyard.</i>

30:03.886 --> 30:05.888
(TOOLS CLANGING AND WHIRRING)

30:12.895 --> 30:15.815
JACKSON: Everything go okay?
Yeah, great.

30:16.565 --> 30:19.068
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
What the hell is this now?

30:19.235 --> 30:21.904
Hostages.
When did that become part of the plan?

30:22.363 --> 30:26.242
I say we kill them now and throw them
off the boat but no one listens to me.

30:26.408 --> 30:28.744
Yeah, well, killing kids
is never part of the plan.

30:28.911 --> 30:32.414
No, it's not. We'll split them up
and shut them up. Let's go.

30:32.832 --> 30:36.001
MURRAY:
Just hold... Hold him.

30:36.168 --> 30:38.379
Darren!
DARREN: Aah!

30:39.004 --> 30:40.256
LILLY: No!
Boss man. Boss man.

30:40.422 --> 30:43.008
She's got one of these.
Give it. No.

30:49.431 --> 30:50.766
Can't have these on my boat.

30:53.227 --> 30:54.937
Take her.

30:55.563 --> 30:57.106
LILLY:
Let me go.

30:57.273 --> 30:58.816
(LILLY GRUNTS)

31:03.904 --> 31:07.283
How much longer?
I'd say no longer than three hours.

31:07.449 --> 31:09.243
Good. Let's go.

31:17.376 --> 31:18.627
(DARREN GRUNTING)

31:21.881 --> 31:22.965
(COUGHING)

31:23.132 --> 31:25.134
MURRAY:
Cazel, enough.

31:25.926 --> 31:26.969
Come on, man.

31:27.136 --> 31:28.762
(COUGHING)

31:30.347 --> 31:32.600
Fuck you, man.

31:33.726 --> 31:36.812
You touch Lilly and I'll fucking kill you!

32:04.590 --> 32:05.799
(TWIG SNAPS)

32:57.476 --> 32:59.061
Hold it.

33:03.315 --> 33:07.152
I got no trouble with you.
My sister is missing.

33:07.403 --> 33:09.655
I got trouble with that.

33:19.081 --> 33:20.374
Where is she?

33:25.671 --> 33:28.090
She's in the old ferry.

33:28.257 --> 33:29.717
Okay?

33:30.384 --> 33:31.552
(GUN COCKS)

33:35.514 --> 33:36.932
(CHUCKLES)

33:44.231 --> 33:47.276
But it really doesn't matter
to you now, does it?

33:50.612 --> 33:53.115
Up, up, up.

34:10.632 --> 34:12.634
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

34:15.429 --> 34:18.223
JAKE: <i>I'm in the forest near
Grayson's junkyard. No sign of Lilly.</i>

34:18.389 --> 34:20.809
<i>I think she's on the old Cascadia.
Headed there now.</i>

34:20.976 --> 34:21.976
Talk to Hark?
<i>Yeah.</i>

34:22.143 --> 34:24.188
I'm waiting for him out by Route 37.

34:24.353 --> 34:27.649
Tell him he'll find some bodies
north of the junkyard into the trees.

34:27.815 --> 34:30.819
Grown men, 30s. See if he can ID them.
Okay.

34:30.985 --> 34:34.406
He's gonna want some backup.
It's not safe out here. You understand?

34:34.572 --> 34:37.159
Yes. No, I understand, Jake.

34:37.326 --> 34:41.288
Just find her, okay. Just find her.
Talk to you in a bit.

34:47.460 --> 34:49.505
Shit.

34:50.130 --> 34:54.842
Darren! Darren!

35:17.199 --> 35:18.534
Psst.

35:21.078 --> 35:22.996
MAN: Drop your weapon.
Drop your weapon.

35:23.163 --> 35:26.458
Agent Wells, FBI. Drop your weapon.

35:27.042 --> 35:28.627
Do it.

35:34.591 --> 35:36.468
Hands on your head.

35:37.928 --> 35:39.555
You okay?

35:39.721 --> 35:40.931
(GROANS)

35:48.188 --> 35:51.525
What we got here is Jake Carter,
4670 Grandview Road.

35:51.692 --> 35:53.610
Local boy, huh?

35:55.404 --> 35:57.906
Sergeant, USMC.

35:58.073 --> 35:59.908
Active duty?

36:00.450 --> 36:02.661
What are you doing?
My sister's been abducted.

36:02.828 --> 36:04.288
Your sister?

36:06.874 --> 36:09.710
WELLS: (OVER RADIO) <i>Thompson,
get to the forest at Grayson's junkyard.</i>

36:09.877 --> 36:12.754
<i>I got a Marine here telling me
there's three dead bodies out there.</i>

36:16.008 --> 36:18.010
(INDISTINCT POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

36:18.177 --> 36:21.680
Call the state police.
WOMAN: No need for that.

36:22.055 --> 36:25.267
Special Agent Thompson, FBI.
You must be Chief Harkin.

36:25.434 --> 36:26.977
That's right.

36:27.227 --> 36:30.230
We got three bodies here and two kids
missing. Possibly abducted.

36:30.397 --> 36:32.357
Two kids missing?

36:32.524 --> 36:34.443
One of them is my little sister.

36:35.360 --> 36:37.946
All right, you two need to come
with me.

36:49.625 --> 36:51.168
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

36:51.627 --> 36:53.128
THOMPSON:
This way.

36:53.462 --> 36:55.130
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

36:59.468 --> 37:02.679
That's gonna be the maximum.
WELLS: What can that penetrate?

37:04.348 --> 37:05.974
Amanda Carter.

37:06.558 --> 37:09.394
Chief Harkin.
I'm Special Agent Wells.

37:09.561 --> 37:13.190
We believe your sister and her friend
are being held on the old Cascadia.

37:13.357 --> 37:16.777
I don't understand. What's going on?
It's complicated.

37:19.655 --> 37:22.616
Look, I'm sorry we can't treat this
strictly as a kidnapping.

37:22.783 --> 37:24.493
There's a lot more at play here.

37:24.660 --> 37:29.164
Jonas Pope has been on our watch list for some time.
He is not your usual extremist.

37:29.331 --> 37:32.334
He was raised by a loving middle-class
family in Spokane.

37:32.501 --> 37:36.004
His father leveraged their home
to pay for his college education.

37:36.171 --> 37:39.800
Pope earned his doctorate in philosophy
from Seattle Pacific.

37:39.967 --> 37:43.178
Parents had all their savings wrapped up
in the market. It collapsed.

37:43.345 --> 37:46.098
They got hit hard, lost their house.
His dad killed himself.

37:46.265 --> 37:49.184
A year later, his sister was diagnosed
with ovarian cancer.

37:49.351 --> 37:52.479
She was dropped from her insurance carrier
when she hit stage Ill.

37:52.646 --> 37:55.274
Pope flew to Spokane to meet
with the insurance adjuster.

37:55.440 --> 37:58.360
He pulled a .22, shot her in her face.
Jesus.

37:58.527 --> 38:01.280
From there, he went into hiding
thanks to Galen Jackson.

38:01.446 --> 38:04.199
Jackson's leader of a small militia group
out of Billings, Montana.

38:04.366 --> 38:07.327
Anti-establishment radical, gun fanatic,
weapons expert.

38:07.494 --> 38:12.541
They're preparing for some kind of attack
involving RDX. A very powerful explosive.

38:12.708 --> 38:13.959
AMANDA:
Okay, I get it.

38:14.126 --> 38:17.254
I'd like to know how you plan to rescue
my sister and her boyfriend.

38:17.421 --> 38:20.299
We're going in.
JAKE: I can help you.

38:20.465 --> 38:24.469
Infiltration-extraction. It's what I do.
Not here. My men, my men only.

38:24.636 --> 38:27.889
You just storm in with our sister inside?
We're waiting for a signal.

38:28.056 --> 38:29.141
HARKIN:
From who?

38:29.308 --> 38:31.476
A reliable source.
Undercover?

38:31.643 --> 38:34.229
Last night, he told us of this
hideaway on the Cascadia.

38:34.396 --> 38:37.566
But he still hadn't learned
the location of the attack.

38:38.275 --> 38:40.527
We haven't heard from him since.

38:42.112 --> 38:44.573
Now, if you'll excuse me.

38:51.830 --> 38:55.500
- So how do I look?
- I'd shoot you.

38:58.378 --> 39:00.589
Great work, boys.

39:01.006 --> 39:02.883
Great work.

39:09.765 --> 39:11.224
Gentlemen.

39:12.184 --> 39:15.854
Everything that we have worked for
ends today.

39:18.857 --> 39:23.278
Our target is an engine of greed...

39:23.445 --> 39:26.073
...a cancer to our society.

39:27.157 --> 39:29.284
By the end of this day...

39:29.868 --> 39:32.454
...our voices will be heard.

39:33.246 --> 39:34.790
As one.

39:41.296 --> 39:42.881
As one.

40:00.816 --> 40:02.818
(DEVICE BEEPING)

40:13.912 --> 40:15.330
What is it?

40:15.831 --> 40:18.125
Somebody's making a call.

40:19.292 --> 40:21.294
(BEEPING CONTINUES)

40:33.306 --> 40:34.516
(BEEPING RAPIDLY)

40:36.685 --> 40:37.853
(BEEPING STOPS)

40:48.738 --> 40:50.365
MAN:
Yeah, I know.

40:50.532 --> 40:53.034
Yeah. I know.
I'm doing my best, all right?

40:53.201 --> 40:56.455
Yeah, I'm doing my best. It's impossible.
These guys aren't gonna...

40:56.621 --> 40:57.873
Hang up.

40:59.708 --> 41:00.792
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

41:00.959 --> 41:03.712
Look, it's not what you think.
Who were you talking to?

41:04.254 --> 41:06.214
My girlfriend down in Tacoma.

41:08.717 --> 41:12.220
She's pregnant. All right?
I was just calling to check on her.

41:12.387 --> 41:15.140
Four months in. Last time we spoke,
she had stomach pains.

41:15.307 --> 41:17.893
It's all I was doing. I'm
not bullshitting you.

41:18.685 --> 41:21.188
The rules are the rules.
Stop. Wait.

41:21.938 --> 41:24.483
I'm with you on this, Pope. I'm all in.

41:24.649 --> 41:27.819
I was just calling to check on my girl.
That's all I was doing.

41:28.445 --> 41:29.488
Redial.

41:29.905 --> 41:32.240
What?
Redial.

41:32.949 --> 41:34.367
All right.

41:36.703 --> 41:37.746
(LINE RINGING)

41:37.913 --> 41:38.914
I wanna hear it.

41:39.873 --> 41:41.875
(LINE RINGING OVER SPEAKERPHONE)

41:42.250 --> 41:47.255
WOMAN: <i>What happened? I lost you.</i>
Yeah, I'm sorry. We had a bad connection.

41:47.422 --> 41:52.802
<i>I'm seeing my doctor in the morning.
Gonna run some tests. Another ultrasound.</i>

41:53.178 --> 41:58.099
<i>Is this the number I can reach you at?</i>
I'm gonna have to check back with you.

41:58.266 --> 42:01.186
I'm gonna have to go now, babe. Okay?
<i>Okay.</i>

42:01.353 --> 42:03.271
<i>I love you, babe.</i>
I love you too.

42:03.438 --> 42:04.981
<i>Bye.</i>

42:15.200 --> 42:19.246
Next time you want to contact her,
talk to me first.

42:19.412 --> 42:20.747
Okay?

42:20.914 --> 42:22.249
Yeah.

42:24.834 --> 42:26.503
Yeah, okay.

42:33.718 --> 42:36.221
Come on! Let me out!

42:44.521 --> 42:47.774
Let me out!

42:50.151 --> 42:52.612
This can't be much fun for you.

42:53.321 --> 42:54.906
I'm sorry.

42:56.241 --> 42:58.243
You and your friend.

42:58.410 --> 43:00.579
What were you doing
out there today?

43:02.622 --> 43:05.417
Hoping for some privacy.

43:06.751 --> 43:08.503
Seems like
we crashed your party.

43:08.670 --> 43:10.005
(SCOFFS)

43:10.171 --> 43:12.674
Seems we crashed yours.

43:14.843 --> 43:16.094
Hm.

43:24.436 --> 43:26.605
Do you like rich people?

43:27.480 --> 43:31.026
Rich people. Do you like them?
I don't know.

43:31.192 --> 43:33.778
Who is the richest person you know?

43:34.946 --> 43:39.075
Come on, simple question.
Who is the richest person you know?

43:39.951 --> 43:43.371
Um... My friend's dad.

43:43.538 --> 43:46.207
He's a contractor.

43:46.374 --> 43:51.463
He makes like $300,000 a year.
Okay.

43:51.630 --> 43:53.882
Okay. I don't mind that sort of rich guy.

43:54.049 --> 43:57.927
He's doing something for society.
He builds houses.

43:58.094 --> 44:00.221
People actually live in houses. Right?

44:01.181 --> 44:04.225
There are others out there
that make 10 times, 50 times that...

44:04.392 --> 44:06.978
...by doing absolutely nothing.

44:08.104 --> 44:10.398
Nothing for society.

44:10.857 --> 44:13.068
They just move money around.

44:13.526 --> 44:17.489
But here's the real kicker.
